    "title": "Creating a Trigger"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Reality Composer supports five types of triggers: Tap, Scene Start, Proximity To",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Camera, Collide, and Notification. In Reality Composer’s Behavior pane, you click",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or tap inside the dashed box representing a trigger to specify the set of conditions",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "or events that cause that trigger’s behavior to fire.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Respond-to-taps-and-touches",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Respond to taps and touches",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Select the Tap trigger when you want a behavior to fire in response to the user tapping",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "a specific object or objects. After adding a tap trigger to the behavior, select",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the object or objects in your scene that you want the user to interact with. If you",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "accidentally select an object that you don’t want, click or tap it a second time",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to deselect it. When you’re finished making your selection, press the Done button.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "To make further changes to the affected objects, press the Choose button to return",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to selection mode.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "You can only use tap triggers for detecting single taps with one finger. To",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "detect more complex scenarios, such as double-taps, long presses, or multiple-finger",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "taps, use a notification trigger and then use ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/releasenotes/MacOSX/WhatsNewInOSX/Articles/MacOSX10_10.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40014484-SW20",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "or ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/SwiftUI",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " gesture detection. For more",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "information, see ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/creating-a-trigger#Fire-a-behavior-from-code",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Tip",
          "style": "tip",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Fire-a-behavior-immediately",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Fire a behavior immediately",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Select the Scene Start trigger if you want a behavior to fire as soon as your scene",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "is loaded and displayed to the user. You would commonly used this type of trigger",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to set the starting state; for example, to hide objects you don’t want visible at",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "first, or to initiate animations to run immediately.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Fire-behaviors-when-the-user-is-near-an-object",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Fire behaviors when the user is near an object",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Select the Proximity To Camera trigger if you want a behavior to fire whenever the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "camera—and, therefore, the user—gets close to specific objects in your scene. Specify",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "how close the user must get by using the Distance slider on the trigger. If you then",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "select the trigger, a green sphere is displayed around the affected objects to represent",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the specified distance. You can also drag the sphere to change the distance visually.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "creating-a-trigger-1",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Respond-to-object-collisions",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Respond to object collisions",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Select the Collide trigger if you want a behavior to fire whenever specific objects",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "collide with other objects in your scene, or when objects collide with detected real-world",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "surfaces.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The target of a collide trigger must participate in your scene’s physics",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "simulation. If you select an object that does not participate, Reality Composer prompts",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "you to enable it.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Fire-a-behavior-from-code",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Fire a behavior from code",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Select a Notification trigger to fire a behavior from code you write in Xcode. Notification",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "triggers are a good option when none of the other trigger types meet your needs.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "When you create a notification trigger, Xcode automatically generates the code needed",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to activate the behavior.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To trigger a notification, call the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "post()",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function on the generated notification.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "If, for example, your scene has a Notification trigger called ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SpinBox",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", as shown",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in the figure below, trigger that behavior from your code like this:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "myScene.notifications.spinBox.post() "
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "creating-a-trigger-2",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
